<br>
All comments appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garrathmoore>Garrath Moore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 674<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 2:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Seeking Epic guidance</span><hr size=1> What level are you? How good is your guild? Do you have a lot of friends?<br>
<br>
There are 3 parts of the quest where you will need help, repeatedly for 2 of them<br>
<br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Veneril Sathir </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->- Iksar necro in KC.  3 groups of 60+ with a good tank, one or two good chanters a few healers and a lot of DPS will destroy him.<br>
<br>
Check out the library for Claud's writeup.  I have done the fight using his technique 6 times and have not had a problem once. <br>
<br>
He drops the Gnarled Staff once every 2-3 fights.  He also drops Kunark legs, which means plenty of people will be happy to help you.  Additionally since it is KC, if you are short on a class there is likely someone in the zone who will help you out.  I have actually recruited several people into my guild including two great rangers that way.<br>
<br>
You can track VS by typing &quot;/wh all ranger 45 55&quot; then finding one in KC and asking if VS is up. Worked for me every time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
He procs an unresistable 1500pt lifetap on anyone he hits.  Keep the MT on one side, keep the other melee on the other side, keep the MT runed and count to 10.  After 10 seconds, open up with everything you have.  <br>
<br>
He has about 16k hp, but can lifetap enough to be about a 30k hp mob.  If he does, you probably have lost.  If he is not dead in 90 seconds, call for evac and camp out because your not going to win.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Phinigel Autropos </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->- Phinny or &quot;that damn fish&quot;.  One good group or 2-3 so so groups (55+) You can invis all the way to his lair once you figure out the way. The path is also posted here in the library.  He has 4 guardian seahorses. Get a monk to split pull them. Once they are dead, pull phinny.  <br>
<br>
Killing Phinny is much easier than getting to him. Don't waste time trying to rebuff and wait for mana after killing the seahorses. If you have a decent force down there, he will be dead shortly anyway.  He drops the Blue Crystal Staff once every 5-10 times.  <br>
<br>
He is the easiest mob but rarest drop, having about 15k hp.  A 65 wiz and 65 paladin in my guild (hardly uber by any stretch) duoed their way down to phinny and killed him.  Several times.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Broken / Enraged Golem.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Take the sprocket Kandin gave you and head to Fear.  Eventually, you will find him up.  He resides under a bell due east of the zone in.  He is level 65 and is straight melee. He is slowable and once slowed anyone can tank him.  <br>
<br>
He has about 150k hp so bring some DPS with you. He drops the Green Oil which you turn back in to Kandin for the Staff of Gabstik.<br>
<br>
He only drops the Oil and he drops it every time.  The hard about him is finding him up at the same time you have enough people on to commit to clearing a good portion of Fear.<br>
<br>
All the rest is just run around work.  Hope that helps.<br>
